The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Tiruchirappalli, Aug. 24 (PTI): Six of 45 people have lost their eyesight after being allegedly administered contaminated eye drops during a cataract operation at a private hospital. Thirty-nine others have complained of loss of vision.           
	A team on Saturday visited the hospital in Perambalur to inspect the operation theatre and collect samples of the eye drop. Patients from different villages underwent the operation during a camp jointly conducted by a blindness prevention society and the hospital.                   
	 Coimbatore (PTI): A part-time courier service employee has been arrested for allegedly withdrawing more than Rs 50,000 using a debit card, that was to be posted to Calcutta.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Taslima Nasreen is likely to leave India for a European country because her movement here is severely restricted for her security, sources said. The Bangladeshi author had returned to India from Sweden early this month.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has ruled that a soldier cannot claim disability pension for an injury that did not occur on army duty.                                                                                                                         
